<h1>
  My COVID rules
</h1>
<p>
  This page describes how I personally prefer to behave during the COVID-19 pandemic.
</p>
<p>
  It's just a snapshot of how I feel now: it will change over time as the situation changes.
</p>
<p>
  The fact that I choose to behave this way does not imply any judgement of people who choose to behave differently.
</p>

<section>
  <h2>
    I am <strong>comfortable</strong> meeting multiple people outside
  </h2>
  <p>
    I prefer to keep at least <strong>an arms-length</strong> distance when meeting people outside
  </p>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>
    I am <strong>mostly comfortable</strong> meeting one person inside
  </h2>
  <h2>
    I am <strong>mostly not comfortable</strong> meeting multiple people inside
  </h2>
  <p>
  I prefer to keep at least <strong>2 metres</strong> disance when meeting people inside
  </p>

  <p>
    The following things make me <strong>more comfortable</strong> when meeting people inside:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Good airflow, keeping distance, people wearing masks
    </li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    The following things make me <strong>uncomfortable</strong> when meeting people inside:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
    Lots of people, spending an extended amount of time indoors
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>
    I wear a mask in the following situations:
  </h2>
  <p>
    Indoors when keeping distance is hard - specifically: in the supermarket, on public transport
  </p>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>
    I prefer to greet people by:
  </h2>
  <p>
    Waving, self-hugging or touching feet
  </p>
</section>
